Strong share price on offerings stabilization and on- track new business; Stay Neutral on lack of earnings upward revisions

StarPower reported 2Q25 results on Aug 27 which beat consensus after misses for several quarters. StarPower's share price is up \(30\%\) in the past one month (vs the SSE Index up \(10\%\) ), which we attribute to earnings stabilization, on- track new business and better investment sentiment in the tech sector. Maintain Neutral, raise Dec- 25 PT to Rmb89, based on \(27x\) 2026E P/E (prior Rmb75.0, based on \(22x\) 2026E P/E). Our target multiple increase reflects the above factors. However, we do not suggest investors chase the stock and we haven't seen any signs of meaningful upward revisions in consensus earnings. Competition for traditional businesses, such as IGBT and SiC, remains fierce and we believe new businesses (GaN, MCU, AI server power semi) will take time to break out.

- 2Q25 review. Net profit of Rmb172mn beat JPME and consensus by \(6\%\) and \(23\%\) . Revenue of Rmb1.0bn was up \(11\%\) QoQ and met JPME and consensus. GM of \(29.2\%\) still declined 1.2ppts QoQ and 2.0ppts YoY, and missed consensus of \(30.5\%\) , reflecting depreciation and competitive pressure.

- 2H25 outlook. StarPower indicated its auto revenue to grow HoH. It guided for in-house SiC chip IDM line (capacity: 5kwpm) to reach full utilization rate by end 2025. It retained its guidance of more than doubling auto SiC revenue in 2025. Industrial revenue saw a one-time recovery in early 2Q, but it lacks sustainability, especially as small clients face soft demand. The solar PV industry had pull-in demand in 1H25 but could face negative impacts in 2H25. Depreciation cost will likely grow slightly HoH in 2H25 (depreciation-to-sales ratio \(6.2\%\) in 2024, and \(9.3\%\) in 1H25).

- Notable areas. 1) Product development. StarPower indicated its auto GaN drive module for auto inverters will be adopted from 2026, its auto MCU will start small volume shipments from the end of 2026, and it has \(>800V\) auto SiC module solutions (for \(>1200V\) EVs). 2) Server and data centers. StarPower has power-semi businesses via domestic and international power supply companies for traditional server power and data center equipment. The company is developing products (IGBT, SiC MOS, GaN, etc.) for AI server power and data centers and expects product launch in 2026. However, revenue generation shall be even later. 3) Overseas business. Non-Asia business was \(7.3\%\) of the revenue mix in 1H25. StarPower has indicated its robust design-wins of auto inverter IGBT and SiC modules for local OEMs in Europe, India, North America, etc, which are expected to fuel its overseas revenue expansion during 2026-30. StarPower has kicked off construction of a module packaging facility in Malaysia. 4) Home appliance inverter IPM: StarPower remains confident of seeing strong revenue growth in 2026 and 2027, after production

Maintain Neutral, Dec- 25 PT of Rmb89, based on 27x 2026E P/E. However, we do not suggest investors chase the stock and we haven't seen any signs of meaningful upward revisions in consensus earnings. Competition for traditional businesses, such as IGBT and SiC, remains fierce and we believe new businesses (GaN, MCU, AI server power semi) will take time to break out.
